    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="4">
            <title>Installing the Cylinder Head</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before cylinder head installation, check
                        <hotlnk document="eges2651_SVCPROC004.xml" xrefid="svcproc004">cylinder sleeve
                            protrusion</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two lifting eyes with four bolts (M12 x 25) onto cylinder head. Tighten bolts to
                    the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_S265APPB01.xml" xrefid="S265APPB01" appearance="hottext">standard torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and dry the cylinder head gasket surface. Also use the correct size tap to clean
                    head bolt holes in the crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650558" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing alignment dowels</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install or verify that alignment dowels are in the top of the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650559" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH05/H05007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing cylinder head gasket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment dowels</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new cylinder head gasket over the alignment dowels.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650560" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh08/H08068.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Lowering cylinder head onto crankcase</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach an
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_1.xml" xrefid="Safety06" appearance="hottext">appropriate hoist and
                        lifting hooks to the lifting eyes</hotlnk>. Carefully lower the cylinder head onto the
                    crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650561" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Lubricating cylinder head mounting bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, verify that the cylinder head bolts have been checked for signs of
                        excessive stretch. Bolts that do not thread into the
                        <hotlnk document="eges2651_108.xml" xrefid="t2650505">head bolt thread gauge</hotlnk>
                        freely must be replaced. If bolts are reused that do not pass this test, the bolts may break
                        during the tightening procedure.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use chlorinated solvents on cylinder head bolts. Parts should be clean, dry, and free
                        of any chemical residue other than engine oil.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate threads and bolt flange of all 26 cylinder head bolts with clean
                    engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all of the cylinder head mounting bolts finger tight only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque all cylinder head bolts per the following procedure and in the specified
                    sequence.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
